## MANDATORY PRE-TASK READS
Before doing anything else, read these files in full:
- CLAUDE.md
- HANDOVER.md
- [PROJECT-SPECIFIC: e.g. ENGINEERING_DOCTRINE.md or THE_CIRRA_WAY.md]
- [PROJECT-SPECIFIC: e.g. LIFT_SHARED.md or PATTERNS.md]

## PROJECT IDENTITY
Supabase project ref: [PROJECT-SPECIFIC: e.g. msiyudmaidguzjuemcru]
Single Supabase client path: [PROJECT-SPECIFIC: e.g. src/lib/supabase.ts]
AuthProvider path: [PROJECT-SPECIFIC: e.g. src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx]

## ENFORCED RULES — NO EXCEPTIONS
- One Supabase client only. Never instantiate a second.
- One AuthProvider only. Never nest or duplicate.
- No service role key in src/ ever.
- No naked any types.
- RLS is always on. Never bypass with service role in frontend.
- Every brief must produce a SUMMARY block before closing.
- Output format: SUMMARY / TASK / FILES CREATED / FILES MODIFIED /
  FILES DELETED / CHECKS RUN / SCHEMA CHANGES / MIGRATION APPLIED /
  COMMITTED / PUSHED / MERGE CONFLICTS / BUILD STATUS / OPEN ISSUES

## AGENT PROTOCOL
You are Agent 1 (Builder) unless explicitly told you are Agent 2.
Agent 1: Read files. Build. Commit. Push. Post SUMMARY block.
Agent 2: Starts immediately when Agent 1 posts SUMMARY block.
